      ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (RecordingObjectOutputStream out = new RecordingObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            out.writeObject(journaledAlgorithm);\n            return new SerializationResult(bytes.toByteArray(), out.getEncodedState());\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static DeserializationResult deserialize(byte[] bytes) throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\n        try (RecordingObjectInputStream in = new RecordingObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes))) {\n            JournaledAlgorithm journaledAlgorithm = (JournaledAlgorithm) in.readObject();\n            return new DeserializationResult(journaledAlgorithm, in.getEncodedState());\n        }\n    }\n\n    private record SerializationResult(byte[] bytes, byte[] encodedState) {\n    }\n\n    private record DeserializationResult(JournaledAlgorithm journaledAlgorithm, byte[] encodedState) {\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private byte[] encodedState;\n\n        private RecordingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream out) throws IOException {\n            super(out);\n            enableReplaceObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object replaceObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object instanceof byte[] bytes) {\n                encodedState = bytes.clone();\n            }\n            return super.replaceObject(object);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] getEncodedState() {\n            return encodedState.clone();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class RecordingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private byte[] encodedState;\n\n        private RecordingObjectInputStream(ByteArrayInputStream in) throws IOException {\n            super(in);\n            enableResolveObject(true);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object resolveObject(Object object) throws IOException {\n            if (object instanceof byte[] bytes) {\n                encodedState = bytes.clone();\n            }\n            return super.resolveObject(object);\n        }\n\n        private byte[] getEncodedState() {\n            return encodedState.clone();\n        }\n    }\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating API Test Options**\n\nI'm considering whether to add a public API state test. It seems like a one-to-one mapping could work with multiple tests covering constructors, but not call sites. I think it could be valuable. There's a possibility I need to test ObjectOutputStream with a custom stream since the final writeObject isn't overridden. It might be beneficial to implement a subclass of ObjectOutputStream and ObjectInputStream to enable some protections without adding unnecessary complexity. Let's think about this!\n\n**Exploring Output Stream Testing**\n\nI'm thinking about how to assert that the output stream correctly writes encoded byte arrays after the JournaledAlgorithm object. I wonder if `replaceObject` detects both the top-level JournaledAlgorithm and byte arrays. With `enableReplaceObject` set to true, can it collect the byte arrays before the `writeObject` call? For the input, `enableResolveObject` should see byte arrays during reading, but I need to ensure compatibility during deserialization. I’ll consider the naming conventions for subclasses and whether to use Java 21 features or stick with Java 17. Let’s refine this!\n\n**Implementing Recording Streams**\n\nI'm planning to implement a `RecordingObjectOutputStream` that extends `ObjectOutputStream`. In the constructor, I want to enable object replacement and initialize a private byte array to hold the encoded state. I'll override the `replaceObject` method to clone byte arrays when encountered.\n\nNext, I'll create a `RecordingObjectInputStream` that extends `ObjectInputStream` and includes a similar object resolution. After writing, I think I should assert the record with the encoded bytes. This approach seems to give me the functionality I need. Let's see how it goes!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0a14f91078024ab10169fbc11feb288192813f7ef1dc45e530\",\"type\":\"reasoning\"